<p class="p">The precipitation suitability index was used to evaluate the precipitation suitability of potato in Northern China. Itwas expressed as follows [
 <xref rid="pone.0203538.ref007" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">7</xref>]: 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0203538.e003" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0203538.e003.jpg" id="pone.0203538.e003g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M3" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">When</mi>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
     <mi class="mi">E</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi class="mi">m</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">,</mo>
     <mi class="mi">S</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     <mo class="mo">/</mo>
     <mi class="mi">E</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi class="mi">m</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(3)</label>
 </disp-formula>
 <disp-formula id="pone.0203538.e004" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0203538.e004.jpg" id="pone.0203538.e004g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M4" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">When</mi>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     <mo class="mo">≥</mo>
     <mi class="mi">E</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi class="mi">m</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">,</mo>
     <mi class="mi">S</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mi class="mi">E</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi class="mi">m</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">/</mo>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(4)</label>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">S(R)</italic> was the precipitation suitability index of potato; 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic> was the precipitation in the specific growth period of potato; 
 <italic class="italic">ET</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">m</italic>
 </sub> was the physiological water requirement of potato during the potato growth season and defined as 
 <italic class="italic">K</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">c</italic>
 </sub>×
 <italic class="italic">ET</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">0</italic>
 </sub>, where 
 <italic class="italic">ET</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">0</italic>
 </sub> was the reference evapotranspiration calculated using the FAO Penman–Monteith method (FAO) [
 <xref rid="pone.0203538.ref007" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">7</xref>,
 <xref rid="pone.0203538.ref027" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">27</xref>] with 
 <italic class="italic">K</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">c</italic>
 </sub> as crop coefficient that depended on the growth stage (
 <xref rid="pone.0203538.t002" ref-type="table" class="xref">Table 2</xref>) [
 <xref rid="pone.0203538.ref028" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">28</xref>].
</p>
